    {
      "id": "0d40d1fbee6c05dfde990438b816dea2f97ed150",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 117,
        "name": "Andreas Dilger",
        "email": "adilger@thelustrecollective.com",
        "username": "adilger"
      },
      "date": "2013-10-15 15:50:15.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1: I would prefer that you didn't submit this\n\n(8 inline comments)\n\nI like the idea of this patch, but it needs a few improvements before it can land.  The main improvement would be to make this OBD_FAIL check also work for ZFS, since I bet it is even slower than ldiskfs.  It may be that using 1MB writes instead of 1kB writes will already speed up these tests noticeably for ZFS.  In Jinshan's patch http://review.whamcloud.com/5164 it appears that this is OSD neutral, but is a lot more complex than this patch.\n\nIf this patch isn't actually dependent on http://review.whamcloud.com/4388 (which it doesn't appear to be) then it should be submitted from a separate branch so that these two patches can land independently.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
