          "email": "alexey.zhuravlev@intel.com",
          "date": "2012-10-25 09:14:29.000000000",
          "tz": 240
        },
        "subject": "LU-2225 tests: skip data writes in few tests",
        "message": "LU-2225 tests: skip data writes in few tests\n\nfew tests need to fill filesystem or just generate a lot\nwrites. this usually take quite long. this patch introduces\nOBD_FAIL_OST_SKIP_BIO. when it's set osd_submit_bio() skips\nwrites. also, fast_dd() is added to t-f which sets this\nfail_loc and drops D_TRACE as the latter decreases CLIO\nperformance a lot.\n\nsanity/64b on a local setup:\n(dgb=full)\t\t\t- 223s\n(dbg=-trace,-dlmtrace)\t\t- 76s\n(dbg=0)\t\t\t\t- 61s\n(skipio,dbg=-trace,-dlmtrace)\t- 46s\n(skipio,dbg=0)\t\t\t- 27s\n\nTest-Parameters: fortestonly testlist=sanity,sanityn\nSigned-off-by: Alex Zhuravlev <alexey.zhuravlev@intel.com>\nChange-Id: I1d7cd2175e6731981d7392d477255f580b945d66\n"
      },
      "branch": "refs/heads/master"
    }
  },
